==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: frankfurter
<hw>frank"fur*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A small cooked sausage of beef
or beef and pork, usually 5 to 6 inches, sometimes as long as 12 inches
in length; called also <altname>frankforter</altname>,
<altname>frankfort</altname>, <altname>frankfurt</altname>. It is
commonly eaten on a roll, called a hot dog bun.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> wiener, hot dog{1}.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frankincense</ent>⟦br⟧
